Thanks for helping develop the next generation of Niagara web applications!

The grunt-niagara plugin is configured to do up to four things: lint your files,
run unit tests, generate docs, and do complexity analysis.

Here are the available tasks:
{{#if jshint}}
grunt jshint: lint all files
                jshint:src - output results to screen
                jshint:ci - output results to a JUnit XML file{{/if}}{{#if karma}}
grunt karma:  do a single test run in Karma using PhantomJS{{/if}}{{#if jsdoc}}
grunt jsdoc:  generate JSDocs{{/if}}{{#if plato}}
grunt plato:  generate complexity analysis docs{{/if}}{{#if watch}}
grunt watch:  spin up in background and run {{#if jshint}}JSHint{{/if}}{{#if karma}} and Karma{{/if}} tests
              whenever a file changes{{/if}}
grunt ci:     perform continuous integration tasks
grunt all:    run everything!

grunt flags:  print a list of available configuration flags
